parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Engine stalling or failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, which can be dangerous and potentially life-threatening.
Timing chain failure can cause catastrophic engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Intake manifold issues can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Electrical/computer system issues can cause engine stalling or failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded, which can be dangerous and potentially life-threatening.
The failure of the front suspension can cause loss of steering and braking, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: and strong vibration in the front of the vehicle
loud pop or jerk when turning
sudden shutdown or stalling of the engine
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.
